This paper is about unsupervised learning of face representations using CNNs. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques for face recognition. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of unsupervised learning, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of video frames, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of face recognition in surveillance scenarios, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
